BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 29 (KCNA) -- The 15th Guyanese 
national seminar on the chuche idea and building of national 
culture was held on April 1 in celebration of the birthday of 
the great leader President Kim Il-song. 
  Dale Bisnauth, minister of Education and Cultural 
Development 
of Guyana, in his opening address said that the chuche idea is a 
great idea that clearly indicates the direction and ways of 
building genuine national culture suited to the specific 
conditions of each country on the basis of the importance of the 
development of national culture in the building of an 
independent, new society. 
  At the seminar ex-Prime Minister of Guyana Hamilton Green 
made a congratulatory address to be followed by a report and 
speeches. 
  Robert Williams, chairman of the Guyanese national committee 
for the study of the chuche idea of Comrade Kim Il-song, in the 
report said the great leader President Kim Il-song has taught 
that only when national culture is developed is it possible to 
consolidate the already-won political independence and 
successfully build an independent national economy. 
  It is an important matter in the building of a new society 
to 
create a popular, true national culture that conforms to the 
people's desire for independence and their idea and emotion, he 
noted. 
  The seminar adopted letters to the great leader President 
Kim 
Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 

